<poem>
<title poet="Bontemps_A">>The Day Breakers</title>
<stanza>
<l n="1">We are not come to wage a strife </l>
<l n="2">With swords upon this hill<punc type="comma">,</punc> </l>
<l n="3">It is not wise to waste the life </l>
<l n="4">Against a stubborn will<punc type="period">.</punc> </l>
<l n="5">Yet would we die as some have done<punc type="period">.</punc> </l>
<l n="6">Beating a way for the rising sun<punc type="period">.</punc></l>
</stanza>
</poem>